r of the Year]] (2): [[1999\u201300 in Scottish football#Individual honours|1999-00]], [[2002\u201303 in Scottish football#Individual honours|2002\u201303]]\n*[[SPFA Players' Player of the Year]] (1): [[2002\u201303 in Scottish football#Individual honours|2002\u201303]]\n*[[Scottish Premier League monthly awards|SPL Player of the Month]] (4): [[Scottish Premier League 2000-01#Monthly awards|November 2000]], [[Scottish Premier League 2000-01#Monthly awards|December 2000]], [[Scottish Premier League 2001-02#Monthly awards|February 2002]], [[Scottish Premier League 2002-03#Monthly awards|January 2003]]\n*Ferguson became a Member of the [[Order of the British Empire]] (MBE) on 17 June 2006.<ref name=MBE2/><ref name=\"mbe\">{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/front_page/5087176.stm |publisher=BBC Sport |title=Thorpe/Ferguson head honours list |date=16 June 2006 |accessdate=27 July 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[http://www.soccerbase.com/players/player.sd?player_id=11073 Barry Ferguson playing stats] at [[Soccerbase]]\n*{{SFA profile}}\n* [http://www.sporting-heroes.net/football/rangers-fc/barry-ferguson-5143/scottish-league-appearances_a14442/ Rangers profile at ''Sporting-Heroes.net'']\n*[http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/authors/barry-ferguson Ferguson's column at the ''Daily Record'']\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{SPFA Young Player of the Year}}\n{{SPFA Players' Player of the Year}}\n{{SFWA Footballer of the Year}}\n{{2006\u201307 PFA Scotland SPL Team of the Year}}\n{{2007\u201308 PFA Scotland SPL Team of the Year}}\n{{Rangers F.C. Hall of Fame}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Managerial positions\n| list1 = \n{{Blackpool F.C. managers}}\n{{Clyde F.C. managers}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ferguson, Barry}}\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Scottish footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Scotland international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Rangers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blackburn Rovers F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Birmingham City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blackpool F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Fleetwood Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Scottish football managers]]\n[[Category:English Football League managers]]\n[[Category:Blackpool F.C. managers]]\n[[Category:Members of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Hamilton, South Lanarkshire]]\n[[Category:Clyde F.C. managers]]\n[[Category:Scottish Professional Football League managers]]\n[[Category:Clyde F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Professional Football League players]]\n[[Category:Kelty Hearts F.C. managers]]\n", "name_user": "Seasider53", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eKelty Hearts", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Barry_Ferguson"}
{"title_page": "Alejandro Strachan", "text_new": "{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Alejandro Strachan\n| image = File:Alejandro Strachan.jpg\n| caption = Alejandro Strachan\n| alma_mater = [[University of Buenos Aires]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = Argentinian\n| field =  [[Computational materials science]] <br> Atomistic and molecular simulation\n| workplaces = [[Purdue University]] <br> [[Los Alamos National Laboratory]] <br> [[California Institute of Technology]]\n| doctoral_advisor =  \n| doctoral_students =\n| known_for  = [[National Nuclear Security Administration|NNSA]] PRISM <br> [[nanoHUB]]\n| prizes = \n| religion = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Alejandro Strachan''' is a scientist in the field of [[computational materials science|computational materials]] and a professor of [[materials engineering]] at [[Purdue University]]. Before joining [[Purdue University]], he was a staff member at [[Los Alamos National Laboratory]].<ref name=\"purdue\">{{Cite web|url=https://engineering.purdue.edu/MSE/people/ptProfile?id=33239|title=Alejandro Strachan \u2014 Purdue University - School of Materials Engineering|website=engineering.purdue.edu|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n\n== Education ==\nStrachan studied physics at the [[University of Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]]. He received his master's of science there in 1995, followed by his PhD in 1998. He then moved to [[Caltech]], first as a postdoctoral scholar and then research scientist, until 2002.<ref name=\"purdue\" />\n\n\n== Research and career ==\nStrachan became a staff scientist in the Theoretical Division of [[Los Alamos National Laboratory]] in 2002, staying until becoming a faculty member at [[Purdue University|Purdue]] in 2005. He became a full professor in 2013.<ref name=\"purdue\" />\n\nStrachan's research focuses on the development of predictive atomistic and molecular simulation methodologies to describe materials, primarily [[density functional theory]] and [[molecular dynamics]]. With these methods he studies problems of technological importance including coupled electronic, thermal, and mechanical processes in nano-electronics, [[MEMS]] and energy conversion devices; thermo-mechanical response and chemistry of [[polymers]], polymer composites, and molecular solids; as well as active materials including [[shape-memory alloy|shape-memory alloys]] and high-energy density materials. He also actively focuses on [[uncertainty quantification]] across the field of materials modelling. \n\nHe previously served as the Deputy Director of the [[National Nuclear Security Administration|NNSA]] Center for the Prediction of Reliability, Integrity and Survivability of Microsystems (PRISM). He is currently co-principal investigator for the Network for Computational Nanotechnology (NCN) and [[nanoHUB]] (with [[principal investigator]] [[Gerhard Klimeck]]) and co-leads the Center for Predictive Material and Devices (c-PRIMED), also with [[Gerhard Klimeck|Klimeck]].<ref name=\"cprimed\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.purdue.edu/newsroom/releases/2013/Q4/new-center-to-lead-purdue-efforts-in-computational-nanotechnology,-materials-and-devices-development.html|title=New center to lead Purdue efforts in computational nanotechnology, materials and devices development|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref><ref name=\"cprimed2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.enterpriseai.news/2013/10/16/purdue-opens-new-center-materials-development|title=Purdue Opens New Center for Materials Development|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nStrachan is also active in education, particularly through [[nanoHUB]], including the fully open and online course ''\"From Atoms to Materials: Predictive Theories and Simulations\"''.<ref name=\"fatm\">{{Cite web|url=https://nanohub.org/courses/FATM|title=nanoHUB-U: From Atoms to Materials: Predictive Theory and Simulations|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n\n== Awards ==\n* Purdue University ''Teaching for Tomorrow'' award, 2007.<ref>{{cite web|author=Purdue Marketing & Media, Purdue University |url=http://www.purdue.edu/provost/faculty/awards/T4T-Recipients.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121202221743/http://www.purdue.edu/provost/faculty/awards/T4T-Recipients.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-12-02 |title=Purdue University Teaching for Tomorrow Fellowship Award Recipients |publisher=Purdue University |accessdate=2013-04-20 }}</ref>\n* The Minerals, Metals and Materials Society Early Career Faculty Fellow Award 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tms.org/society/Honors/EarlyCareer.aspx |title=TMS Professional Honors and Awards: Early Career Faculty Fellow Award |publisher=The Minerals, Metals & Materials Society  |date= |accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>\n* Purdue University College of Engineering Faculty Excellence Award. Team Award: PRISM, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://engineering.purdue.edu/Engr/People/Awards/Institutional/Faculty/2009/ptIndexYear |title=2009 Faculty Awards of Excellence Recipients |publisher=Purdue University College of Engineering |date=2009-04-25 |accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>\n* Purdue University Faculty Scholar (2012-2017)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://engineering.purdue.edu/Engr/People/Awards/Institutional/Scholars |title=University Faculty Scholars - Active Appointments |publisher=Purdue University College of Engineering |date= |accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>\n\n\n== Selected Publications and Editorials==\n* Development of a [[ReaxFF]] reactive interatomic potential for energetic materials and study of shock behavior <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Strachan|first=A.|last2=van Duin|first2= A.C.| last3=Chakraborty| first3=D.|last4=Dasgupta| first4=S.|last5=Goddard III|first5=W.A.| date=2003| title=Shock waves in high-energy materials: the initial chemical events in nitramine RDX|journal=Physical Review Letters|volume=91|issue=9|pages=098301}}</ref>\n* Prediction of polymer properties from [[molecular dynamics]] <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Li|first=C.|last2=Strachan| first2=A.| date=2011| title=Molecular dynamics predictions of thermal and mechanical properties of thermoset polymer EPON862/DETDA| journal=Polymer| volume=52| issue=13| pages=2920-2928}}</ref>\n* Exploration of atomic-level mechanisms in nanoscale memory devices <ref>{{Cite journal| last=Onofrio| first=N.| last2=Guzman| first2=D.| last3=Strachan| first3=A.| date=2015| title=Atomic origin of ultrafast resistance switching in nanoscale electrometallization cells| journal=Nature materials| volume=14| issue=4| pages=440-446}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://phys.org/news/2015-03-simulations-insight-emerging-nanoelectronic-device.html| title=Simulations provide new insight into emerging nanoelectronic device| access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n* Guest editor with [[Gerhard Klimeck]] and [[Mark Lundstrom]] of Special Issue in ''Computing in Science and Engineering'' on \"Cyber-enabled simulations in nanoscale science and engineering\" March/April 2010.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Strachan|first=A.| last2=Klimeck|first2=K.| last3=Lundstrom|first3=M.| title=Cyber-enabled simulations in nanoscale science and engineering| journal=Computing in Science & Engineering| volume=12| issue=2| pages=12-17| date=2010</ref>\n* Guest editor with Stephen Foiles and David McDowell in ''[[Modelling and Simulation in Materials Science and Engineering]]'' for the Focus Issue on Uncertainty Quantification in Materials Modelling\" October 2019.<ref>{{Cite journal| last=Foiles|first=S.| last2=McDowell|first2=D.| last3=Strachan|first3=A.| title=Preface for focus issue on uncertainty quantification in materials modeling| journal=Modelling and Simulation in Materials Science and Engineering| volume=27| pages=080301| date=2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://nanohub.org/courses/FATM From Atoms to Materials: Predictive Theories and Simulations]\n*[https://engineering.purdue.edu/MSE/People/ptProfile?id=33239 School of Materials Engineering Faculty Profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Strachan, Alejandro}}\n[[Category:Purdue University faculty]]\n[[Category:Engineering educators]]\n[[Category:Materials scientists and engineers]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox scientist\n| name = Alejandro Strachan\n| image = File:Alejandro Strachan.jpg\n| caption = Alejandro Strachan\n| alma_mater = [[University of Buenos Aires]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| nationality = Argentinian\n| field =  [[Computational materials science]] <br> Atomistic and molecular simulation\n| workplaces = [[Purdue University]] <br> [[Los Alamos National Laboratory]] <br> [[California Institute of Technology]]\n| doctoral_advisor =  \n| doctoral_students =\n| known_for  = [[NNSA]] PRISM <br> [[nanoHUB]]\n| prizes = \n| religion = \n| footnotes = \n}}\n\n'''Alejandro Strachan''' is a scientist in the field of [[computational materials science|computational materials]] and a professor of [[materials engineering]] at [[Purdue University]]. Before joining [[Purdue University]], he was a staff member at [[Los Alamos National Laboratory]].<ref name=\"purdue\">{{Cite web|url=https://engineering.purdue.edu/MSE/people/ptProfile?id=33239|title=Alejandro Strachan \u2014 Purdue University - School of Materials Engineering|website=engineering.purdue.edu|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n\n== Education ==\nStrachan studied physics at the [[University of Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]]. He received his master's of science there in 1995, followed by his PhD in 1998. He then moved to [[Caltech]], first as a postdoctoral scholar and then research scientist, until 2002.<ref name=\"purdue\" />\n\n\n== Research and career ==\nStrachan became a staff scientist in the Theoretical Division of [[Los Alamos National Laboratory]] in 2002, staying until becoming a faculty member at [[Purdue University|Purdue]] in 2005. He became a full professor in 2013.<ref name=\"purdue\" />\n\nStrachan's research focuses on the development of predictive atomistic and molecular simulation methodologies to describe materials, primarily [[density functional theory]] and [[molecular dynamics]]. With these methods he studies problems of technological importance including coupled electronic, thermal, and mechanical processes in nano-electronics, [[MEMS]] and energy conversion devices; thermo-mechanical response and chemistry of [[polymers]], polymer composites, and molecular solids; as well as active materials including [[shape-memory alloy|shape-memory alloys]] and high-energy density materials. He also actively focuses on [[uncertainty quantification]] across the field of materials modelling. \n\nHe previously served as the Deputy Director of the [[National Nuclear Security Administration|NNSA]] Center for the Prediction of Reliability, Integrity and Survivability of Microsystems (PRISM). He is currently co-principal investigator for the Network for Computational Nanotechnology (NCN) and [[nanoHUB]] (with [[principal investigator]] [[Gerhard Klimeck]]) and co-leads the Center for Predictive Material and Devices (c-PRIMED), also with [[Gerhard Klimeck|Klimeck]].<ref name=\"cprimed\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.purdue.edu/newsroom/releases/2013/Q4/new-center-to-lead-purdue-efforts-in-computational-nanotechnology,-materials-and-devices-development.html|title=New center to lead Purdue efforts in computational nanotechnology, materials and devices development|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref><ref name=\"cprimed2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.enterpriseai.news/2013/10/16/purdue-opens-new-center-materials-development|title=Purdue Opens New Center for Materials Development|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nStrachan is also active in education, particularly through [[nanoHUB]], including the fully open and online course ''\"From Atoms to Materials: Predictive Theories and Simulations\"''.<ref name=\"fatm\">{{Cite web|url=https://nanohub.org/courses/FATM|title=nanoHUB-U: From Atoms to Materials: Predictive Theory and Simulations|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n\n== Awards ==\n* Purdue University ''Teaching for Tomorrow'' award, 2007.<ref>{{cite web|author=Purdue Marketing & Media, Purdue University |url=http://www.purdue.edu/provost/faculty/awards/T4T-Recipients.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121202221743/http://www.purdue.edu/provost/faculty/awards/T4T-Recipients.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-12-02 |title=Purdue University Teaching for Tomorrow Fellowship Award Recipients |publisher=Purdue University |accessdate=2013-04-20 }}</ref>\n* The Minerals, Metals and Materials Society Early Career Faculty Fellow Award 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tms.org/society/Honors/EarlyCareer.aspx |title=TMS Professional Honors and Awards: Early Career Faculty Fellow Award |publisher=The Minerals, Metals & Materials Society  |date= |accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>\n* Purdue University College of Engineering Faculty Excellence Award. Team Award: PRISM, 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://engineering.purdue.edu/Engr/People/Awards/Institutional/Faculty/2009/ptIndexYear |title=2009 Faculty Awards of Excellence Recipients |publisher=Purdue University College of Engineering |date=2009-04-25 |accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>\n* Purdue University Faculty Scholar (2012-2017)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://engineering.purdue.edu/Engr/People/Awards/Institutional/Scholars |title=University Faculty Scholars - Active Appointments |publisher=Purdue University College of Engineering |date= |accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>\n\n\n== Selected Publications and Editorials==\n* Development of a [[ReaxFF]] reactive interatomic potential for energetic materials and study of shock behavior <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Strachan|first=A.|last2=van Duin|first2= A.C.| last3=Chakraborty| first3=D.|last4=Dasgupta| first4=S.|last5=Goddard III|first5=W.A.| date=2003| title=Shock waves in high-energy materials: the initial chemical events in nitramine RDX|journal=Physical Review Letters|volume=91|issue=9|pages=098301}}</ref>\n* Prediction of polymer properties from [[molecular dynamics]] <ref>{{Cite journal|last=Li|first=C.|last2=Strachan| first2=A.| date=2011| title=Molecular dynamics predictions of thermal and mechanical properties of thermoset polymer EPON862/DETDA| journal=Polymer| volume=52| issue=13| pages=2920-2928}}</ref>\n* Exploration of atomic-level mechanisms in nanoscale memory devices <ref>{{Cite journal| last=Onofrio| first=N.| last2=Guzman| first2=D.| last3=Strachan| first3=A.| date=2015| title=Atomic origin of ultrafast resistance switching in nanoscale electrometallization cells| journal=Nature materials| volume=14| issue=4| pages=440-446}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| url=https://phys.org/news/2015-03-simulations-insight-emerging-nanoelectronic-device.html| title=Simulations provide new insight into emerging nanoelectronic device| access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n* Guest editor with [[Gerhard Klimeck]] and [[Mark Lundstrom]] of Special Issue in ''Computing in Science and Engineering'' on \"Cyber-enabled simulations in nanoscale science and engineering\" March/April 2010.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Strachan|first=A.| last2=Klimeck|first2=K.| last3=Lundstrom|first3=M.| title=Cyber-enabled simulations in nanoscale science and engineering| journal=Computing in Science & Engineering| volume=12| issue=2| pages=12-17| date=2010</ref>\n* Guest editor with Stephen Foiles and David McDowell in ''[[Modelling and Simulation in Materials Science and Engineering]]'' for the Focus Issue on Uncertainty Quantification in Materials Modelling\" October 2019.<ref>{{Cite journal| last=Foiles|first=S.| last2=McDowell|first2=D.| last3=Strachan|first3=A.| title=Preface for focus issue on uncertainty quantification in materials modeling| journal=Modelling and Simulation in Materials Science and Engineering| volume=27| pages=080301| date=2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://nanohub.org/courses/FATM From Atoms to Materials: Predictive Theories and Simulations]\n